title: OMG My Life is Changed!
description:
Well, I never would have guessed that I would take to the drums like I have over the last week. After my last video, my placement "grounded" me for three weeks. Basically I could not leave the property. I could go outside but not to my play or church or any outside activities. I was DEVASTATED. But then, something came in my head to get a small drum kit. So, against my better judgement I spent my last money on a Kickboxx suitcase drum set. It came in a few days and....my life was changed. Playing the drums is such a good outlet for me. It is physical yet musical and I can just play from my heart whatever rhythms I feel. I was so in love and obsessed that I decided to sell the first kit, along with some other items to get a real proper kit. This is that video. So, what was meant to bring me down, those 3 weeks, ended up being a blessing. I am now the proud owner of a set of vintage Premier birch wood drums. Thank you to everyone who left such kind, caring and understanding messages. I read them all. I know so many people were praying for me. I made it through and you helped me. Thank you. 
If you are looking to learn the drums, I highly recommend this channel: @RobBeatdownBrown 
You can follow my drum progress on my music channel, link below. #premierdrums 

My music channel: https://www.youtube.com/c/ThePianoGirl

title: Costuming, I've Been DREADING This. The Enchanted Bookshop (Part 2)
description:
I feel pretty vulnerable whenever I have to where a uniform or costume that I did not pick out. I worry it will fit me, or have itchy materials, or look a way that I don't want to look. So I knew this was going to be difficult, but...I didn't know it would make me feel this bad. I didn't really show it in my face, but this was hard. Thankfully I know that my worth is not in how I look in a dress, but is in Jesus. I feel better today and I am ready to share part 2 of my theater experience!! #theenchantedbookshop

title: Madness! My First Time at the Goodwill Bins
description:
This week my friend took me to the Goodwill Bins. There was a lot of chaos in there, and unspoken rules, but she filled me in and helped me out. I had to handle a lot of noise and learn to be assertive...because people WILL push you out of the way. In the end I got so much for just $14!  Not all of it was retro but I got a lot of cool toys and electronics. Plus I had fun and can say I survived the Goodwill bins lol, which really should be a t-shirt. Shout out to @HairyTornado for teaching me how to be a better deal hunter. If you enjoy thrifting I think you would love his channel.
#thrifting #goodwill #retrogames #retrotoys

title: Shouting At Leaves by Jennifer Msumba- Book Trailer
description:
Shouting At Leaves was written by autistic author Jennifer Msumba
Pre-Order here: https://amzn.to/3k48uqk
Learn more about the author: https://www.jennifermsumba.com/

“I have lived through some horrible experiences, all in the name of treatment. But there was one thing I never let those people steal from me, and that was my spirit.”

Shouting At Leaves takes the reader on the journey of its autistic writer from toddlerhood to adulthood. With humor and grace, this book walks you through the mind and experiences of Jennifer as she navigates the world of family, friendships and school life. It places you with her as she is confined in the mental health system, and you will cheer her on as she not only survives but takes on a new life of freedom and joy in the end. She shares stories, tips, and strategies to equip you to be your own champion, and to build around you people who are loyal and true.

#autism #autismbooks #booktrailer #judgerotenbergcenter

description:

Today on Now, That's Interesting! I interview friend and fellow filmmaker Scott Klumb. Scott was diagnosed with autism later in life, and in this interview we talk about how that effects a person who is on the spectrum and how it affected him, both good and bad.

Scott was also a winner in the @TheDisabilityFilmChallenge last year (Best Editor) and he has a new documentary, Autism: One Man's Journey, releasing for free on April 8, 2021.

Lyrics to Finally Home:
five years old, dirt under my nails
throwing rocks at the bullies
saying you’re not a girl
scared of my own shadow I
was in my own world

longing 
to be free from the trap in my mind
where the black hole of circles
distorted the time
but I fought with a champions heart
determined to shine

days burn
years pass
they say it gets worse before better
found my
own path
i wish I had seen this letter

you will be strong
you will be loved
you will be, a person whose people
are loyal and true

don’t be scared Love
don’t hide your face, in your hands
look to the sun
it’s where you belong
keep moving on

all grown up now
life’s looking good
got a place of my own
i’m where I belong
i’m finally home

now I am strong
and I am loved
i am the person, whose circle of people
are loyal and true

i’m not afraid now
got my face towards the sun
i’m where I belong 
i’m happy and strong
i’m finally home

©2020 Jennifer Msumba

title: I Almost Fell In

title: We Are On Lockdown (Day 1)
description:
***Song lyrics below*** Well, they did it, they placed the facility where I live on a lockdown where we can't go out (except to the doctor) and also no visitors are allowed in. When I got the news this morning I was REALLY upset. But then after talking to some friends, I realized I can take this opportunity to rest and also make content to help us get through this time. I decided I will make a daily vlog for this time and just keep you up to date on how I'm handling all the changes as well as it's a chance for us to encourage each other. We are going to make lemonade out of lemons! My porch swing: https://amzn.to/2U2P5aV (Affiliate)

description:

description:
Today I learned what it is like to collaborate with others on a project. Something I have always tried to avoid since I was in school, and we would be assigned group projects. Teamwork is hard, even if you don't have autism. It's a lot of communication and compromise. But I had a goal and a vision and I did my best to accomplish that. I want to show you to never abandon your goals just because you think you have limitations. You can achieve more than you think you can!

title: How To Make Spiced Pumpkin Seeds
description:
Ingredients:

-2 cups raw whole pumpkin

-1 1/2 tablespoons butter or margarine (melted)

-2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce

-1/2 teaspoon salt

-1/8 teaspoon garlic salt

preheat over to 275

combine all ingredients in a bowl

place in shallow baking dish

bake for 1 hour

These are really delicious and make a great fall time treat

description:
i wake up in the morning i feel like the walking dead
gotta have a drink to get the cobwebs out my head

its coffee its coffee its how i stay ahead

i stumble to the kitchen
with my hair a total mess

top it off with cinnamon

i take a sip and damn 
now i’m feeling kind of good
